        "enrichmentDataCollection": "<p>Access Remote system to validate if log disabled. </p><p> If access not available - go to analysis</p><p> </p><p><span style=\"background-color:#F0F2F4;\">Identifies when the exchange audit logging has been disabled which may be an adversary attempt</span> to evade detection or avoid other defences.</p><p>Operation performed is “ Set-AdminAuditLogConfig” cmdlet. Visit <a href=\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/module/exchange/set-adminauditlogconfig?view=exchange-ps#:~:text=This%20cmdlet%20is%20available%20in,administrator%20audit%20logging%20configuration%20settings\">Link</a> </p><p><b><span style=\"background-color:#F0F2F4;\">Purpose</span></b><span style=\"background-color:#F0F2F4;\">: </span></p><p><span style=\"background-color:#F0F2F4;\">Looks for any suspicious attempts to disable the Exchange Audit logs. </span>Only users belonging to (\"Admin\",\"DcAdmin\") has the privilege to Disable Exchange Auditlog.  </p><p><span style=\"background-color:#F0F2F4;\">Log Sources: Office365</span> logs</p><p><span style=\"background-color:#F0F2F4;\">Events of interest: OfficeActivity</span> logs</p>",
