        "enrichmentDataCollection": "<p>Gather information on Process name, host, execution anomaly.</p><p>Check intelligence sources to see if this is a known pattern for an attack/threat</p><p>Execute Analysis on process and anomaly</p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"color:black;background-color:white;\">Identifies anomalous spike in frequency of executions of sensitive processes which are often leveraged as attack vectors. The query leverages KQL built-in anomaly detection algorithms to find large deviations from baseline patterns. Sudden increases in execution frequency of sensitive processes should be further investigated for malicious activity. </span>Tune the values from 1.5 to 3 in series_decompose_anomalies for further outliers or based on custom threshold values for score</p><p><b><span style=\"color:black;background-color:white;\">Purpose: </span></b>Identifies anomalous increase in frequency of executions of sensitive processes. </p><p><b>Some of the processes monitored are </b></p><p><b>powershell.exe, cmd.exe, wmic.exe, psexec.exe, cacls.exe, rundll.exe.</b></p><p><b>Potential Log Sources</b>: SecurityEvents </p><p><b>Events of interest</b>: Event ID 4688</p><p style=\"text-align:left;\"><b><span style=\"\">Malware Incident Procedure</span></b> </p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"\">This procedure will take place in any scenario which involved a malware infection file or behavior which was blocked by CyberArk</span></p>",
