        "detectionSourceLogic": "<p>Collect events that correlate with changes to account objects and/or permissions on systems and the domain, such as event IDs 4738, 4728 and 4670.[Monitor for modification of accounts in correlation with other suspicious activity. Changes may occur at unusual times or from unusual systems. Especially flag events where the subject and target accounts differ or that include additional flags such as changing a password without knowledge of the old password.</p><p>Monitor for use of credentials at unusual times or to unusual systems or services. This may also correlate with other suspicious activity.</p><p>Monitor for unusual permissions changes that may indicate excessively broad permissions being granted to compromised accounts.</p>",
        "enrichmentDataCollection": "<p>Alert if user account is added to built in domain local or global group. Verify Authorization</p><p></p><h1><span style=\"color:#6888C9;\"><b>User account added to built-in domain local or global group</b></span></h1><p><b>Purpose</b>:</p><p>Identifies when a user account is added to a privileged built-in domain local or global group, such as the Enterprise Admins, Cert Publishers, or DnsAdmins</p><p><b>Potential Log Sources</b>: SecurityEvents </p><p><b>Events of interest</b>: SecurityEvent</p><p><b>Logs Collection prerequisites</b>:</p><p>Windows logs with Event ID:</p><ul>\n<li><p><a href=\"https://www.ultimatewindowssecurity.com/securitylog/encyclopedia/event.aspx?eventID=4728\"><u>4728</u></a> - A member was added to a security-enabled global group.</p></li>\n<li><p><a href=\"https://www.ultimatewindowssecurity.com/securitylog/encyclopedia/event.aspx?eventID=4732\"><u>4732</u></a> - A member was added to a security-enabled local group.</p></li>\n<li><p><a href=\"https://www.ultimatewindowssecurity.com/securitylog/encyclopedia/event.aspx?eventID=4756\"><u>4756</u></a> - A member was added to a security-enabled universal group.</p></li>\n</ul><p><span style=\"background-color:#F6F6F6;\">This event is only logged on domain controllers.</span><b>Use </b></p>",
