        "detectionSourceLogic": "<p>CyberReason is an end point protection application that generates Malware Alerts when triggered. \r</p><p> Ferguson manages their CR environment.  MalWare Policies are jointly configured by CR and FEI for the purposes of \rgenerating an alert.  Alerts are generated via the CR application sent through Logstash via API into Sentinel for \r</p><p>investigation.  The SOC has the ability to query CR directly with L1 accounts and L2 has the ability to isolate and \rinvestigate </p>",
        "enrichmentDataCollection": "<p>The events and investigation will be conducted within cyberreason application.  Detection\r will be accomplished by the SOC and Incident generated in the CDC.  If incident is Medium or lower severity, escalate to \rL2 for any clarification, generate email notification and notify site lead.  If incident is High or critical severity, immediately\r escalate IAW Fergusons Incident response plan and activate X-Matters notification process.  \r\r</p><p>Once investigation validates Malware, L1 should immediately isolate any end point utilizing the features within\r CyberReason.  Any server is to be considered a high severity and should never be isolated with fergusons express permission.\r</p><p>Once isolated, investigation should look for infected items in the end point or server and extrapulate that data utilizing CRs \rcapability.  Engage the Cyber Threat Intelligence team for clarification and informaiton as necessary</p>",
