        "automationMaturity": "Manual Playbook",
        "detectionSourceLogic": "<p>SailPoint is an application used to manage life cycle events, which is running batch jobs at noon and midnight eastern time. these batch jobs create accounts or terminate accounts, with dependencies on other system. This use case is monitoring access to their LOCAL ADMINISTRATOR ACCOUNT (SPADMIN). This account is used as a break glass method for administering SailPoint in extreme situations. Access to spadmin is controlled by the CyberArk application with credentials being story in a Cyber Ark Vault. Customer wants CyberArk monitored for control to credential access, generating an alert in the CDC when those credentials are accessed. </p>",
        "enrichmentDataCollection": "<p>Integration Name: PAN Autofocus Domain</p><p>Integration System Name: PAN Autofocus</p><p>System Detail: Cloud based system, The AutoFocus™ API extends the ability to query the threat intelligence cloud through a programmatic, RESTful API. You can integrate this API into a third-party service, application, or script that accesses AutoFocus outside of the web portal. API responses are in JSON or XML-based STIX format.</p><p>Integration System Type: Threat Intelligence</p><p>Integration Use: Enrich alert through Domain query (may be for suspicious domain or for phishing detection)</p><p>Input: Domain Name from Alert.</p><p>Output of Integration: CDC Alert enrichment including (Domain reputation in autofocus, risk rating, date of rating.)</p><p>Brief explain of usage: Assists the analyst in verification that a suspicious email is a phishing attack by including the sender’s domain reputation in the alert.</p><p></p><h1>Pre Knowledge</h1><p><b><u><span style=\"color:black;background-color:white;\">VIP impersonation</span></u></b></p><p><span style=\"color:black;background-color:white;\">Email phishing attack known as </span>Business Email Compromise (BEC) or CEO</p><p><span style=\"color:black;background-color:white;\">Fraud. CEO Fraud is a scam in which cybercriminals spoof company email</span></p><p><span style=\"color:black;background-color:white;\">accounts to impersonate executives or colleagues. They attempt to</span></p><p><span style=\"color:black;background-color:white;\">deceive an employee or colleague into executing unauthorized wire</span></p><p><span style=\"color:black;background-color:white;\">transfers, sending out confidential tax information, or even purchasing gift</span></p><p><span style=\"color:black;background-color:white;\">cards.</span></p><p><b><u><span style=\"color:black;background-color:white;\"></span></u></b></p>",
