        "enrichmentDataCollection": "<p><b>Known Manganese IP and UserAgent activity</b></p><p><b>Purpose</b>: </p><p>Manganese IP threat actor is Specialised in exploiting VPN vulnerabilities to gain access to targeted networks, which allows a remote unauthenticated attacker to send specially crafted requests that allow read access of arbitrary files on the VPN servers. This includes access to databases that the VPN server uses to track sessions, cleartext credentials, and NTLM hashes. </p><p>Once the attacker gained VPN DB access, they will </p><ul>\n<li><p>Connections to the VPN using obtained session IDs in order to resume or takeover an existing valid session</p></li>\n<li><p>Locally stored accounts cracked and leveraged to connect to VPN services</p></li>\n<li><p>Connections to the VPN’s administrative interface using obtained sessions IDs, possibly in an attempt to conduct remote code execution against newly connecting VPN clients</p></li>\n<li><p>Login attempts against other corporate resources, such as e-mail, using credentials that were stored by the VPN server database in the clear </p></li>\n</ul><p></p>",
