        "description": "<p>Account management lifecycle usually states that unused account must be removed. This implies that all existing accounts should be observed being used. Therefore, this use case will monitor inactive accounts and will have has multiple goals:</p><p></p><ul>\n<li><p>Provide an overview of accounts that are inactive for an extensive period of time and should be removed</p></li>\n<li><p>Trigger an alert every time a successful logon is registered for an inactive account</p></li>\n<li><p>List of activities (outside of a successful connection) of an inactive account</p></li>\n</ul><p></p><p></p><p>While the first point is to comply with best practices, the other two behaviors can highlight an attacker trying to gain control of an account that was forgotten.An account is being defined as active when it authenticated successfully onto a system. Thus, an account that was not able to connect to a system in the last 90 days will be considered inactive.</p><p><br></p>",
